Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light red-brown. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Also secondary stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '11' and '202'. Name Alexandros. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum ABC 0314.01
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (8)
